<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUSS LEADABRAND; HISTORIAN WROTE ABOUT THE OLD WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Russ Leadabrand, 74, writer and historian who chronicled California and the 
Old West. A native of Illinois, he grew up in Pasadena and Dinuba in the San 
Joaquin Valley.He attended Columbia University, the University of New Mexico 
and USC. Leadabrand began his career writing for Pasadena-area newspapers, 
becoming travel editor and a daily columnist for the Pasadena Star News, posts 
he held until his retirement in 1971. He also wrote features for men's 
adventure magazines, Arizona Highways, Sunset and Desert magazines. Leadabrand, 
an expert on the desert and weekend getaway destinations, developed a 
long-running column for the automobile club magazine Westways called "Let's 
Explore a Byway." He also wrote guidebooks about the West and edited an annual 
book on deserts published by the Westerners, a group of writers and historians 
of which he was a member. On Monday in Cambria. 
</P>
