NOEL POINTER; CONTEMPORARY JAZZ VIOLINIST AND COMPOSER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Noel Pointer, 40, contemporary jazz violinist and composer twice nominated for 
Grammy awards.Pointer made his solo debut at age 13 as a classical violinist 
performing with the Symphony of the New World Orchestra in New York. He also 
appeared with the Chicago Chamber Orchestra and the Detroit Symphony. Pointer 
also worked with theater orchestras, including those at the Apollo Theatre and 
Radio City Music Hall. He recorded seven solo albums, and two -- "All My 
Reasons" and "Direct Hit" -- were nominated for Grammys. Another album, 
"Phantazia," went platinum. On Tuesday in New York City of a stroke. 
