<HEADLINE>
<P>
PUTTING COUNCIL VOTES TO THE TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your "On the Issues" question of Oct. 28 was, "Should the public be allowed to 
sue City Council members because of the votes they cast?" 
</P>
<P>
 I believe the answer is a wholehearted "yes!" -- especially if and when these 
votes are tainted, politically motivated, unfair, predetermined and in 
violation of public policy and the law. No one -- not even politicians -- 
should be held to be above the law. 
</P>
<P>
 HARRIET K. BILFORD 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge 
</P>
