<HEADLINE>
<P>
BERNSON STANDS UP TO CRA 'BUREAUCRACY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Congratulations to City Councilman Hall Bernson for standing up to an 
intractable bureaucracy, the Community Redevelopment Agency. 
</P>
<P>
 After many meetings, lots of input, approval by community leaders in the 
hardest-hit area of the city by the earthquake, a proposal to meet the needs of 
the Northridge, Granada Hills and Chatsworth areas was submitted.Included were 
safeguards so that a Downtown Los Angeles agency could not, once again, use its 
economic power for sociological and economic experimentation. 
</P>
<P>
 Unfortunately, the CRA was more interested in power than in responding to the 
needs of the 12th Council District in the San Fernando Valley. Happily, 
Councilman Bernson understands what happens when the CRA takes over an area 
without limitations. Finally, he said no to the CRA power grab, to protect the 
jobs and residents of his district. This took courage. 
</P>
<P>
 Now it is time to rein in the power of the CRA and change state laws so that 
local communities can control their own destinies. That was the message of the 
election on Nov. 8. It is too bad the CRA did not hear it. 
</P>
<P>
 STEPHEN R. FRANK 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 
</P>
