<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUSTICA RIDGE WINS HOLLYWOOD PARK FEATURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rustica Ridge, an 8-1 shot ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye, came from far off the 
pace Thursday to win the $35,000 feature race at Hollywood Park by 1 1/4 
lengths over Leasears. 
</P>
<P>
 Rustica Ridge, carrying 117 pounds, covered 1 1/8 miles on Hollywood Park's 
turf course in 1:52 and paid $19.80, $8.20 and $4.80. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was one of three on the day for Delahoussaye. 
</P>
<P>
 Leasears, ridden by Gary Stevens and carrying 115 pounds, finished a 
half-length ahead of Slick Silk and returned $4.80 and $3. 
</P>
<P>
 Slick Silk, ridden by Chris Antley and carrying 114 pounds, was three-quarters 
of a length in front of 19-10 favorite Musical Pal and paid $3.80 to show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
