<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEPPERDINE RALLY FALLS SHORT, 61-58 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pepperdine overcame a 13-point second-half deficit before faltering in the 
last 1 1/2 minutes of a 61-58 loss to San Diego State on Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 "We dug ourselves a big hole and scratched back but could not get over the 
top," said Pepperdine Coach Tony Fuller."We had an opportunity to take the lead 
but failed to capitalize on our chance." 
</P>
<P>
 Pepperdine (2-7) trailed, 46-33, with 9:54 to play after Dion Gray made a free 
throw to cap a 7-0 run by San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
 But Gerald Brown, who scored 19 of his 21 points in the second half, scored 
eight during a 10-1 run that pulled the Waves to within 47-43 and made a 
three-point basket that tied the score at 54-54 with 3:03 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego State (5-3) took the lead for good, 57-56, with 1:05 to play on a 
free throw by Marc Carter, who led the Aztecs with 18 points and 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego State missed three of six free throws in the last 12 seconds but 
twice retained possession with offensive rebounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
