<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; SANTA MARGARITA BEATS TORREY PINES IN TITLE GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alan Krist had 15 points and 14 rebounds to lead Santa Margarita to a 43-35 
victory over Encinitas Torrey Pines in the title game of the San Dieguito 
tournament Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Krist was named the tournament's most valuable player. J.C. Timmons added 10 
points for Santa Margarita (10-0), ranked ninth in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sacramento Tracy tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 62, Davis 45 -- Josh Lightman scored 27 points and Dave Ogas added 17 
for Edison (5-6) in the consolation final. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague play: 
</P>
<P>
 Los Amigos 54, Century 43 -- Los Amigos made all 29 of its free throw attempts 
and outscored Century, 19-8, in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Kit Ratanaphoulee, Geronimo Cortez and John Elsaeser each scored 12 points to 
lead the Lobos (4-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 57, Sunny Hills 53 -- Brian Seaton scored 19 points, Matt Bodiford 
13 and John Norum 10 points to lead visiting Brea (8-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park 66, Orange Lutheran 54 -- Towan Oliver scored 20 points and Ruben 
Gaffo added 17 to lead visiting Buena Park (5-6). Sonny Madsen had 14 points 
for Orange Lutheran (2-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 59, Honolulu St. Louis 43 -- Dan Galvanoni scored 14 points 
for host Capistrano Valley (8-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Loara 50, Anaheim 47 -- Tony Moss had a game-high 13 points to lead visiting 
Loara (6-4). Newport Harbor 58, Saddleback 46 -- Will Rankin scored 12 points 
to lead Newport Harbor (6-6). 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 63, Westminster 50 -- Eli Engle scored 21 points and had 11 
rebounds and Mike Castaneda had 15 points for host San Clemente (5-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 90, University 67 -- David Burgess scored 36 points for Woodbridge, 
which outscored University, 50-33, in the second half. Freshman Eric Palmer had 
15 points and seven assists and Nathan Scoggin had 15 points for the Trojans 
(3-8). 
</P>
