<HEADLINE>
<P>
EIGHT PLAYERS WITH TIES TO O.C. TO PLAY FOR U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eight players with Orange County ties will represent the United States in the 
North American Junior Water Polo Championships Dec. 28-30 at El Toro High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine's Ryan Bailey, Brandon Stout, a UCLA player from El Toro High, and 
goalkeeper Craig Thomas, an Air Force player from Esperanza High, will play for 
the U.S. junior team.The junior team is coached by Foothill High Coach Jim 
Brumm. 
</P>
<P>
 Goalkeeper Greg Stoll (El Toro), Brian Brown (Foothill), Brian Heifferon 
(Servite), Rob Mattivi (Servite) and Jerry Smith (Servite) play for the U.S. 
youth team. 
</P>
<P>
 Two teams each from Mexico and Canada also will compete. There are two 
sessions daily, starting at 10 a.m. and 3 p.m. The title game is scheduled for 
5:30 p.m. Dec. 30. 
</P>
