<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Debra Can; Mike Cronan, WILGOREN,; Jeff Bean 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 THE WALRUS DIP: December is hardly the month that most of us think about 
taking a swim in the ice-like Pacific. But the "Walruses" of the Newport Beach 
Athletic Club are doing it for a cause -- raising funds to help the 
homeless.About 100 of them will run two miles in the sand this morning at 
Corona del Mar State Beach -- for corporate sponsors -- then take a dip to 
"earn their tusks."... Says spokeswoman Judy Cooper: "In the name of love, they 
gamble their sanity." 
</P>
<P>
 RED HOT GIFT: Chad Smith, drummer for the Red Hot Chili Peppers, recalls his 
first drums: "Baskin-Robbins ice cream cartons." So he was delighted to meet a 
16-year-old Huntington Beach youth with cystic fibrosis Thursday when the young 
man, named Loren, received a sheer blue $3,000 Pearl drum set. It's the same 
kind owned by Smith, Loren's favorite drummer. . . . Smith's visit in Fountain 
Valley and the drums were made possible through the Make-A-Wish Foundation. 
Says Loren: "It's the best Christmas present you can ever get." 
</P>
<P>
 LOADED FOR BEAR: For years Brad Wright of San Clemente has set up an 
award-winning Christmas display in his front yard. But sometime early Thursday, 
someone swiped the mechanical polar bear that's been one of its central 
features for seven years. . . . Wright, who says it would have taken three 
people to cart it off, is offering a $250 reward, no questions asked: "I'd 
rather get back into the spirit of the season." 
</P>
<P>
 TONIGHT: Saxophonist Boney James (F37) at 8, Galaxy Concert Theatre, 3503 S. 
Harbor Blvd., Santa Ana. (714) 957-0600. 
</P>
<P>
 WEATHER: Fair today with increasing clouds late tonight. Highs near 70. Lows 
in the upper 40s. (B8) 
</P>
