<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS; ORANGE COUNTY TASK FORCE TAKES AIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Save the Rams task force members on Thursday abandoned their six-month course 
of diplomacy toward the NFL team they're trying to keep in Orange County and 
declared war. 
</P>
<P>
 Save the Rams called a news conference to say it's convinced the Rams will 
strike a deal to move to St. Louis "within 10 days," according to agent Leigh 
Steinberg, co-chairman of the group. 
</P>
<P>
 Committee members, said they'll launch a lobbying assault on NFL owners in an 
attempt to secure the eight votes required to block a move. 
</P>
<P>
 They also criticized the team for a failure to negotiate in good faith, 
questioned its commitment to Southern California fans and accused Ram President 
John Shaw of ignoring efforts to keep the team in Orange County. MIKE 
DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
