yet to be confirmed, girls' Coach Melissa Hearlihy said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls' team would play a nonleague game against Bishop Montgomery and the 
boys' team would face Mission League-rival Loyola. However, formal approval has 
yet to be received from Alemany administrators. 
</P>
<P>
 It was reported Thursday in another newspaper that the doubleheader was a done 
deal. 
</P>
<P>
 "That was entirely premature," Hearlihy said. "Our players hadn't even been 
informed of the possibility. We hadn't received confirmation from Loyola." 
</P>
