<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUOTE ME: OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; OC HIGH ASKS: WHAT'S THE BEST EXCUSE 
YOU'VE EVER GIVEN YOUR PARENTS WHEN YOU'VE BEEN IN TROUBLE? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 " You did it when you were a kid, so why can't I?" 
</P>
<P>
 Ethan Wells, 16 
</P>
<P>
 sophomore, Newport Harbor 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 "I got a ticket for speeding, and I told my parents the reason I was going so 
fast was because I had a foot spasm that caused me to push my foot down on the 
accelerator." 
</P>
<P>
 Brad Thomas, 17 
</P>
<P>
 senior, Irvine 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 "According to my watch, I wasn't an hour late." 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Shipley, 16 
</P>
<P>
 junior, Trabuco Hills 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 "I have no good excuses." 
</P>
<P>
 David Rice, 15 
</P>
<P>
 sophomore, Los Amigos 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 "Once I was out after curfew, and I got caught by the cops. After they called 
home and I was picked up, I told my parents that I (had been) hungry, and 
instead of going upstairs and waking them up by creaking the stairs, I (went 
out) to buy some food." 
</P>
<P>
 Blake Cecil, 17 
