<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARGO JET CRASHED IN ENGLAND; 5 KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Boeing 737 cargo jet owned by Air Algerie crashed Wednesday on approach to 
Coventry airport, killing all five people aboard.Coventry is 94 miles northwest 
of London. 
</P>
<P>
 The crash occurred in a wooded area near a cluster of houses about a mile 
northeast of the airport. Witnesses said the jet snapped a power line and 
damaged some houses before crashing. 
</P>
<P>
 No one on the ground was injured, officials said. 
</P>
