<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; RECYCLE YULE TREES AT DROP-OFF POINTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burbank officials are asking residents to recycle their Christmas trees at one 
of several citywide locations in the weeks following the holidays. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will not, as in past years, have special alley/curbside collections 
to pick up trees this year but rather has scheduled five sites where residents 
can drop them off for composting, said spokeswoman Cinda Cates. 
</P>
<P>
 Trees can be dropped off between 7 a.m. and 4 p.m. Dec. 27 through Dec. 31 and 
Jan. 3 through Jan. 7. 
</P>
<P>
 Sites available for tree drop-off are Brace Canyon Park, 2800 Haven Way; 
Verdugo Park, 3201 W. Verdugo Ave.; McCambridge Park, 1515 N. Glenoaks Blvd.; 
Ralph Foy Park, 3200 W. Victory Blvd.; and Izay/Olive Park, 1111 W. Olive Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents who have been supplied with green recycle containers by the city 
have another option. They can cut up their trees -- after making sure that 
ornaments, lights and stands have been removed -- and place them in the 
containers for pickup on their regular collection days. 
</P>
<P>
 Recycled trees will be turned into mulch and composting material. Flocked 
trees cannot be composted and should be put in residents' black refuse 
containers, officials said.  
</P>
<P>
 The Burbank recycling program, in its fifth year, recycled 78 tons of 
Christmas trees last year. For more information, call the sanitation division 
at (818) 953-6622. JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</TEXT>
