<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SANTA ANA; CHRISTMAS EVE EVENT TO OFFER FREE FOOD, TOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Employees from the Santa Ana Unified School District and the Delhi Community 
Center will provide food and toys for hundreds of needy families and homeless 
children this Christmas Eve, a district spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 During the event, which is co-sponsored by Toys for Tots, volunteers are 
expected to serve about 1,000 meals and give away 800 toys, said John Bennett, 
assistant superintendent of the elementary division. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is free and open to the public. 
</P>
<P>
 District officials advertised the event by distributing flyers at local 
schools, Bennett said. "We sure would welcome anyone in need," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Meals will be served from 11 a.m. to 2 p.m. at Festival Hall, 220 E. 3rd St. 
Donated clothing will also be distributed during the event, he said. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
