<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; GANG SUSPECT HELD IN YOUTH'S SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEOFFREY MOHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gunshots in a Van Nuys neighborhood early Thursday morning led detectives to a 
suspect in last week's shooting death of a 16-year-old North Hollywood youth. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers were staking out several locations near Fulton Avenue and Sherman 
Way, looking for Ray Martinez, 20, when gunfire erupted nearby, said Los 
Angeles Police Detective Charles Uribe. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers saw two men run into an apartment on the 6900 block of Fulton Street, 
Uribe said. 
</P>
<P>
 When officers asked occupants to step outside, they found Martinez among them, 
Uribe said. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no arrests related to the report of gunfire. 
</P>
<P>
 Martinez was taken into custody at about 1:30 a.m. and charged with murder and 
robbery in the shooting death of Marlon Gutierrez of North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 Gutierrez and a friend had been walking on the 12500 block of Vanowen Street 
at about 11 p.m. last Friday when a group of men robbed them at gunpoint. 
Gutierrez was shot when he tried to walk away, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives believe Martinez is a member of a branch of the Mara Salvatrucha 
gang, Uribe said. They believe the gunfire that led officers to Martinez may 
have come from a rival gang. GEOFFREY MOHAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122394-0212 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 110831 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
