<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: SIMI MAN FACES MOLESTATION HEARING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Simi Valley man suspected of molesting three children in fast-food 
restaurants, including two in the San Fernando Valley, is scheduled to appear 
for a preliminary hearing today in Van Nuys, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael John Fellows, 46, was arrested in Los Angeles Dec. 12 following a 
two-month investigation of incidents at a McDonald's and Carl's Jr. in the San 
Fernando Valley and another at a McDonald's in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Fellows is being held in Los Angeles County Jail in lieu of $300,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police, Fellows is accused of molesting a 9-year-old girl in the 
women's restroom of the Carl's Jr. restaurant. The incident at a McDonald's in 
Northridge involved a 4-year-old girl, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident in Simi Valley, which led to the arrest of Fellows, was reported 
Oct. 18. An 8-year-old girl was standing at the sink in the women's restroom 
when a man came in, knelt by her and licked her leg, authorities said. The man 
then asked the girl for a kiss, but she refused and left, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fellows was later identified as a suspect in that incident, police said. Simi 
police shared information they obtained in the case with the Los Angeles Police 
Department, which made the arrest. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
