<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONSUMER BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Espresso Machine Maker Responds to Injuries: A leading espresso machine maker 
will offer corrected operating instructions after reports of injuries caused by 
shattered carafes, the Consumer Product Safety Commission announced this week. 
The agency said Krups North America will voluntarily offer stickers and 
corrected operating instructions for its 1.47 million espresso-cappuccino 
machines, model No. 963, after receiving 57 reports of shatterings, including 
15 injuries.The problem is linked to the position of the filter holder for the 
machine. If it is set in the wrong position, steam pressure may build up with 
enough force to cause the holder to fly out of the machine, possibly shattering 
the glass carafe. Consumers should rotate the filter holder to the "max" 
position. Call (800) 526-5377 to receive revised operating instructions and a 
sticker to put over the "min-max" position. 
</P>
</TEXT>
