CONSUMER BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hearing Aid Maker Settles FTC Complaint: The Federal Trade Commission said 
Beltone Electronics Corp., one of the nation's largest makers of hearing aids, 
has agreed to pay $825,000 in penalties to settle charges of false-advertising 
claims.The agency said the case involved Chicago-based Beltone's marketing of 
its ClearVoice and Voice Enhancer hearing aids. The settlement includes 
provisions to prohibit Beltone from misrepresenting the ability of its hearing 
aids to focus on speech in noise situations, the FTC said. It said the 
settlement also requires Beltone to give refunds to dealers whose customers 
have returned their aids after a trial period and to make certain advertising 
disclosures to help customers understand the limits of the hearing aids. 
</P>
</TEXT>
