ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: NASDAQ SYSTEM DROPS LISTING OF WEST COAST BANCORP'S 
STOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 West Coast Bancorp, a Newport Beach bank holding company, reported that its 
common stock has been deleted from the Nasdaq National Market System, effective 
at the end of trading Thursday, because the bid price no longer met the 
requirements for continued listing. The company said its common stock is 
eligible to trade on the OTC Bulletin Board. 
</P>
