<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trimedyne Inc.: The Irvine medical laser company said it has settled a patent 
infringement lawsuit filed against it by Coherent Inc.  
</P>
<P>
 Trimedyne said that, under the agreement, Coherent dropped its lawsuit, and 
Trimedyne dropped an unfair competition lawsuit against Coherent.Trimedyne said 
it also received a license in orthopedics at a minimal royalty rate. The 
lawsuit had alleged that Trimedyne infringed on three separate Coherent 
patents.  
</P>
<P>
 In a separate announcement, Trimedyne said it is in discussions with 
orthopedic companies for a possible marketing alliance for its orthopedic laser 
and fiber optic delivery systems. 
</P>
