<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Microsemi Corp.: The Santa Ana supplier of custom semiconductor chips posted a 
loss of $2.1 million, or 28 cents a share, for its fiscal year ended Oct. 2. 
That contrasted with profit of $3 million, or 35 cents a share, for the 
previous 12 months, which included a gain of $1.3 million from an accounting 
change.Annual revenue totaled $119.2 million, compared to $123.8 million.  
</P>
<P>
 The company said the 1993 revenue figure included $7.5 million from businesses 
sold either in fiscal 1993 or before the end of fiscal 1994. For the fourth 
quarter, the company recorded a loss of $4.5 million, or 60 cents a share, 
which included an inventory write down of nearly $10 million.  
</P>
<P>
 For the same period a year earlier, the company had a profit of $950,000, or 
11 cents a share. Three-month sales rose 5% to $31.3 million from $29.8 
million. 
</P>
