LESS AT A LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fewer Orange County homeowners are taking losses when they sell their houses 
this year than in 1993, reflecting the trend in Southern California and across 
the state. That pattern is likely to continue, real estate experts say, given 
that home prices are stabilizing. 
</P>
<P>
 Selling at a Loss, 1994* Orange County: 51.1% Southern California: 41.2% 
Statewide: 34.8% *Projection 
</P>
<P>
 On the Upswing 
</P>
<P>
 Although half of Orange County home sellers are taking losses this year, that 
is an improvement from 1993. Across the region, only San Bernardino County is 
showing an increase this year in the percentage of homes sold at a loss. 
