 A TWA jetliner with 112 passengers on board struck a bird Thursday, ripping a 
two-foot hole in the plane's nose and forcing an emergency landing. 
</P>
<P>
 The Boeing 727 bound for St. Louis made a safe landing at Tampa International 
Airport shortly before 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
