<HEADLINE>
<P>
KILLING OF BABIES TESTS DUTCH LAW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Dutch doctors who killed gravely ill newborns face criminal trial in the 
Netherlands in a test case of liberal Dutch euthanasia policy, the Justice 
Ministry said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 One doctor has admitted killing a 3-day-old severely handicapped girl at her 
parents' request. Her brain was only partly developed, she had spina bifida and 
partial paralysis, her limbs were malformed, and she faced a life of pain. 
</P>
<P>
 Justice Minister Winnie Sorgdrager ordered the prosecutions to determine how 
the law applies to cases when a doctor ends the life of a person who is unable 
to ask for death. The law requires doctors to show that a patient was 
terminally ill, in unbearable suffering and had repeatedly asked to die. 
</P>
</TEXT>
